name: Espresso
description: The term espresso means “under pressure” and, according to Ernesto Illy, “the term espresso refers to a request made for the occasion.

name: American coffee
description: Caffè Americano is a type of coffee drink prepared by diluting an espresso with hot water, giving it a similar strength to, but different flavor from, traditionally brewed coffee.

name: Tea
description: Tea is an aromatic beverage prepared by pouring hot or boiling water over cured or fresh leaves.

name: Croissant
description: Often people equate croissants as bread. In fact, croissants are one type of pastry. The basic difference between bread and pastry is that pastry is made from ingredients with high fat content so that the pastry has a flaky texture.

name: Donuts
description: A small piece of fried sweet dough in the shape of a ring covered in candy.

name: Pretzel
description: A crisp biscuit baked in the form of a knot or stick and flavored with salt.

name: Cola Coke
description: Coca-Cola, or Coke, is a carbonated soft drink manufactured by The Coca-Cola Company.
